    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Public API Namespace\n\n### What I found\n- Bun has a consistent pattern for format namespaces: each one lives in `src/bun.js/api/XxxObject.zig` (the JS API wrapper) backed by a parser in `src/interchange/xxx.zig`\n- The wiring goes through 4 files: `BunObject.zig` (Zig side), `BunObject+exports.h` (C++ macro declarations), and `BunObject.cpp` (JSC property table)\n- There is an existing `src/ini.zig` (npm config INI parser, ~16k lines) — **the plan does NOT use it**, per your constraint\n\n### 8 files involved\n\n**Create (3):**\n1. `src/interchange/ini.zig` — self-contained INI parser + stringifier (no import of `src/ini.zig`)\n2. `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` — thin JS API wrapper exposing `parse`/`stringify` on a `Bun.INI` object\n3. `test/js/bun/ini/ini-public.test.ts` — tests for the public API\n\n**Modify (5):**\n4. `src/interchange.zig` — add `pub const ini = @import(...)`\n5. `src/bun.js/api.zig` — add `pub const INIObject = @import(...)`\n6. `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` — 4 targeted edits (lazy property decl, export, getter fn, import)\n7. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` — add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n8. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` — add one row to the `@begin bunObjectTable`\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **Values as strings**: INI is inherently stringly-typed; no type coercion\n- **Tolerant parsing**: malformed lines (no `=`, bad section headers) are silently skipped\n- **GC safety**: uses `MarkedArgumentBuffer` (same as `YAMLObject.zig`) during JS object construction\n- **Stringify**: root-level scalars first, then `[section]` blocks for nested objects",
